I'll add a simple health check endpoint. You can add this to your Express app:

```typescript
app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', uptime: process.uptime() });
});
```

This returns a JSON response with the server status and uptime in seconds.

Sure! A readiness check verifies that all dependencies (like database connections) are available:

```typescript
app.get('/ready', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    await db.ping();
    res.json({ status: 'ready' });
  } catch (err) {
    res.status(503).json({ status: 'not ready', error: err.message });
  }
});
```

This returns 200 when the database is reachable and 503 when it's not.
